  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Mechanism | Add Rack-Pinion - Ball-Screw</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Add Rack and Pinion / Ball-Screw</para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-RackPinion">Rack-Pinion dialog-box</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Terminology</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:115px;">
          <para styleclass="Interface" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Rack -Pinion</text> : </para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:454px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Element">Rack-Pinion</text> is the term for a sliding, linear-gear (<text styleclass="Element">Rack</text>) that is in mesh with a rotating, circular-gear (<text styleclass="Element">Pinion</text>). </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The motion of the two <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Parts</text> are kinematically-related by the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">module</text> and &#160;<text styleclass="VariableName-small">number-of-teeth</text> on the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Pinion</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:115px;">
          <para styleclass="Interface" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Ball-Screw : </text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:454px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Ball-Screw</text> is a device in which a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Screw</text> rotates to move a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Nut</text>, or vice-versa. The Linear-Motion of the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Nut</text> and the rotation of the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Screw</text> are related by the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">lead</text> of the screw-thread. &#160;</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Kinematic State <text style="color:#ff0000;">before</text> you do Add Rack-Pinion.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Either the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> with the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Pin-Joint </text>or the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> with the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Slide-Joint</text> is <text styleclass="VariableName-small" style="color:#ff0000;">not</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName-small">kinematically-defined</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Kinematic State <text style="color:#ff0000;">after</text> you do Add Rack-Pinion.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> with the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Pin-Joint </text>and the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> with the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Slide-Joint</text> are <text styleclass="VariableName-small">kinematically-defined</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_arrow0.gif" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_arrow0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_arrow1.gif"><caption><![CDATA[Kinematics-Tree of the Rack-Pinion]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Rack-Pinion</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> removes </text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">one</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> degrees-of-freedom.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td rowspan="2" style="width:236px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-ADD-RACKPINION-KINEMATICS-TREE.ipp" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="T_Menu"><image src="Red-14-1.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">When the movement of the Pinion will come from the Rack - Driving Rack</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">Before</text> you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Rack-Pinon</text>, the <text styleclass="VariableName">sliding-Part</text> is <text styleclass="Body Text">kinematically-defined and the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">rotating-Part </text>has <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">one</text> degree-of-freedom.</para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">After</text> you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Rack-Pinion,</text> the <text styleclass="VariableName">sliding-Part(Rack)</text> and the &#160;<text styleclass="VariableName">rotating-Part (Pinion) </text>are kinematically-defined, and in one kinematic-chain.</para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="T_Menu"><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">When the movement of the Rack comes from the Pinion - Driving Pinion</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">Before</text> you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Rack-Pinon</text>, the <text styleclass="VariableName">rotating-Part</text> is <text styleclass="Body Text">kinematically-defined and the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">sliding-Part </text>has <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">one</text> degree-of-freedom.</para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">After</text> you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Rack-Pinion,</text> the <text styleclass="VariableName">rotating-Part</text> (Pinion) and <text styleclass="VariableName">sliding-Part (Rack) </text>are kinematically-defined, and in one kinematic-chain.</para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
