          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="Interface2">Result</text> : </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-weight:normal;">The </text><text styleclass="Element">Pinion</text><text style="font-weight:normal;"> is on the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Rotating-Part</text><text style="font-weight:normal;">. </text></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-weight:normal;">The </text><text styleclass="Element">Rack</text><text style="font-weight:normal;"> is on the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Sliding-Part</text><text style="font-weight:normal;">. </text></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text">The <text styleclass="Element">Rack</text> is parallel to the <text styleclass="Element">Line</text><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets" figurelistinclude="0"></image> you select in the <text styleclass="VariableName">Sliding-Part</text>. </para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text">The Pitch-Line of the <text styleclass="Element">Rack</text> is offset from the center of the <text styleclass="Element">Pinion</text> by the <text styleclass="VariableName">Pitch-Circle Radius</text> of the <text styleclass="Element">Pinion</text>.</para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-weight:normal;">The </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Sliding-Part</text><text style="font-weight:normal;"> is now a </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text style="font-weight:normal;"> that is </text><text styleclass="Interface">kinematically-defined</text><text style="font-weight:normal;">.</text></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
